@Retired at last: It looks like the title needs several spelling changes, and we'll be ready to make them, tapping the good assists from pennylrichardsca in deciphering the handwriting.

How could the words differ so much?  The current titles come from a file of captions typed on index cards--the original source of the words might have been either the text that Bain staff wrote on the negative itself, or words on the paper sleeve around the negative. The words are usually similar, but not always the same. 

Until the scans were finished, we hadn't seen what was written on the negatives. With the data on the negatives more visible now, we make improvements!
